  "texts": [
    "The color screening effect increases with the temperature and distance.",
    "As quarkonium dissociation mainly happens in the early stage of the medium evolution with high temperatures, we employ an effective constant in-medium binding energy in the calculation of quarkonium dissociation [219,220].",
    "• Vacuum limit of potential/spectroscopy The vacuum limit of potential is Cornell potential, V (r) = -α c /r + σ r with α c = π/12 and σ = 0.2 GeV 2.",
    "The charm and bottom quark masses are taken as 1.5 GeV and 4.5 GeV, respectively.• Reaction rates Gluo-dissociation, g + ψ → Q + Q, isconsidered as the dominant dissociation process in the QGP for tightly bound quarkonium.",
    "The cross-section, σ Q Q gψ, in vacuum can be derived through the operator product expansion method and was calculated firstly by Peskin and Bhanot [224,225]."
